arts.ttl: Keeper scores in stoppage time to save Leyton Orient in FA Cup
arts.sum: The keeper went up for a free-kick in the ninth minute of stoppage time and got his head to Tom James's delivery to take the second round clash to extra-time. Keeley's moment came as the O's trailed 1-0 at home to National League Oldham Athletic, Manny Monthe scoring on 47 minutes for the non-league outfit.

arts.ttl: Shaun Maloney explains decision to leave out Wigan Athletic star man Thelo Aasgaard
arts.sum: Shaun Maloney has explained the thought process behind starting talisman Thelo Aasgaard on the Wigan Athletic bench for Saturday's 2-0 home defeat to Leyton Orient.

arts.ttl: Wigan Athletic boss on Leyton Orient home defeat - 'It never felt like we were threatening them...'
arts.sum: Shaun Maloney admitted Wigan Athletic paid a high price for an off-day at both ends of the field during the 2-0 home defeat to Leyton Orient.

arts.ttl: REPORT: Wigan Athletic 0 Leyton Orient 2: Tics crash at home with barely a whimper
arts.sum: Wigan Athletic served up one of their worst performances of an increasingly disappointing season as Leyton Orient ran out deserved 2-0 victors at the Brick Community Stadium.

arts.ttl: Wigan Athletic: Four changes in our expected team v Leyton Orient
arts.sum: Paul Kendrick runs the rule over the Wigan Athletic squad and predicts the 11 men who Shaun Maloney will select to start at the Brick Community Stadium against Leyton Orient.

arts.ttl: Former Wigan Athletic man recovering after suffering two strokes
arts.sum: The family of former Wigan Athletic man Tommy Widdrington say he is recovering well after suffering two strokes.

arts.ttl: Wigan Athletic skipper opens up on special relationship unpinning mean streak
arts.sum: Jason Kerr has opened up on his special relationship with Will Aimson that has helped Wigan Athletic become one of the meanest defences in the EFL.

arts.ttl: Wigan Athletic chief sets out 'demands' for January - 'Get it done...'
arts.sum: Shaun Maloney has reiterated his intention to again put 'big pressure' on sporting director Gregor Rioch and head of recruitment Stephen Gormal to make sure Wigan Athletic are ready to come flying out of the blocks in the January transfer window.
